The paper discusses the development of a benchmark suite for deep neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also focuses on evaluating the performance of the benchmark suite on various computing platforms, including GPUs and FPGAs, which falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). Additionally, the paper discusses the architectural statistics of the networks, which falls under the category of computer architecture (cs.AR). The benchmark suite includes convolutional neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision applications (cs.CV), and recurrent neural networks, which are commonly used in natural language processing (cs.LG).
